Title: How Cops Can Get Your Private Online Data
Description: Can the cops get your online data? In short, yes. There are a variety of US federal and state laws which give law enforcement powers to obtain information that you provided to online services. But, there are steps you as a user and/or as a service provider can take to improve online privacy.Law...

Title: Time to start de-Appling – Hi, I'm Heather Burns
Description: I‘ve done such a thorough job of de-Googling that I forgot to show up for a meeting with someone, because I hadn’t checked my Google calendar in ages. (No, they were not amused.) In my defense, I proceeded to explain to them that having de-Googled, I was also in the process of de-Appling, which is a special bonus level that those of us in the UK have unlocked.

Title: The Linux Kernel Looks To "Bite The Bullet" In Enabling Microsoft C Extensions
Description: Two patches queued into the Linux kernel's build system development tree, kbuild-next, would enable the -fms-extensions compiler argument everywhere for allowing GCC and LLVM/Clang to use the Microsoft C Extensions when compiling the Linux kernel

Title: XSLT.RIP - Google are killing XSLT!
Description:
October 24th 2025: Google published the death note:
          Intent to Deprecate and Remove: Deprecate and remove XSLT
          Google will kill XSLT by 2027.
          Google first tried to kill XSLT in July 2013 twelve years ago.
